        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="2oXfcFkHlSiF0renCrEj-8" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;General contract&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;When we develop a smart contract, we will create logic to store the user&#39;s last transaction timestamp when the user calls the smart contract, similar below image.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Inter, sans-serif; white-space-collapse: break-spaces; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ff3333&quot;&gt;But in my system, if the owner does not call our smart contract, they can send a transaction to another smart contract, so we can&#39;t update the last transaction.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
